body: I've tried dist-build/android-armv7.sh, but got no luck.

comment_data.body: These scripts are completely outdated and not maintained anymore. cc: @zoff99
@empirefox do you want to compile for android?

@zoff99 yes. I want to compile with golang. For now I just succeed compiling c-toxcore using the way of [#507](https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore/issues/507). But I cannot find a way to compile using [gomobile bind](https://github.com/golang/mobile).
i dont know anything about golang.
Thanks @zoff99. looks like i must do the experiments by myself.
@empirefox maybe you can get some inspiration from the qTox cross-compile script for windows, https://github.com/qTox/qTox/blob/master/windows/cross-compile/build.sh#L895-L950
I created this [docker repo](https://github.com/empirefox/dockers/tree/master/gomobile-toxcore), and i just built aar for android+gomobile successful.
